---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What fans are compatible?",
    answer: "Any standard 4-pin PWM fan that runs on 12V. This includes popular choices like Noctua NF-A12x25, NF-F12, Arctic P12 PWM, and be quiet! Silent Wings. The board supports up to 4 fans with a combined draw of 2.5A."
  },
  {
    question: "Does it work with 5V fans?",
    answer: "No, the board is designed for 12V fans only. The barrel jack input is 12V DC, which is passed through directly to the fan headers. Using 5V fans requires a separate voltage converter."
  },
  {
    question: "How many fans can I control independently?",
    answer: "Up to 4 fans, each with independent PWM speed control and individual RPM monitoring. Every fan can run at a different speed based on temperature thresholds or manual settings."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need Home Assistant?",
    answer: "Home Assistant gives you the best experience with auto-discovery and dashboard integration, but it's not strictly required. The controller runs standalone with ESPHome firmware - temperature-based automation works locally on the device without any server."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I use it to cool a server rack or network cabinet?",
    answer: "Yes, that's the most popular use case. Mount 120mm PWM fans (e.g. Noctua) in your rack and let the built-in temperature sensor automate fan speed. Many users cool rack-mounted servers, NAS enclosures, and network equipment this way."
  },
  {
    question: "How is firmware updated?",
    answer: "Over-the-air (OTA) via WiFi - no cables needed after initial setup. You can also update via USB-C. The board ships pre-flashed with ESPHome factory firmware."
  },
  {
    question: "Is the hardware open source?",
    answer: "Yes - the ESPHome firmware configs and the hardware schematics are published on GitHub. Only the Gerber/production files are not public. The board also features standard Qwiic/I2C and GPIO expansion ports for custom modifications."
  },
  {
    question: "What sensors are built in?",
    answer: "An HDC1080 temperature and humidity sensor is integrated on the board. You can add external sensors via the Qwiic (I2C) expansion port - for example, an additional temperature probe placed directly in the airflow."
  }
];

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": faqs.map(faq => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": faq.question,
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": faq.answer
    }
  }))
};
---

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

<section class="faq-section">
  <h2 class="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    {faqs.map(faq => (
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">{faq.question}</summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">{faq.answer}</p>
      </details>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
  }

  .faq-heading {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0;
    background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .faq-question::marker,
  .faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-question::before {
    content: "+";
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--sl-color-accent);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  details[open] > .faq-question::before {
    content: "\2212";
  }

  .faq-answer {
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0 1.25rem 1rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
